The course offers an introduction to the ethics of teaching and professional helping, focusing on the issues concerning people and especially children with special needs. The abilities of seeing and analyzing the ethical problems and choices in special/inclusive education and the skills to solve ethical dilemmas will be taught. The course contains the lectures as well as seminars in which discussions on ethics (publications, dilemmas, cases) will be held.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course offers 1) knowledge about professional ethics and responsibility of special education teachers and speech therapists, 2) the skills to solve ethical problems in their everyday work.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The objective of the course is: 1) to increase a sense of responsibility to act ethically as a member of the profession; 2) to learn main principles and regulations of the ethics of special education and scientific research; 3) to develop the abilities of seeing and analyzing the ethical dilemmas and choices; 4) to get the skills for ethical problem-solving.
